Steps

  1. Set working directory and the file path to refer to the appropriate data set.

  2. Set column names from the data set to a continuous varaible measure or discrete variable dimension.

  3. After running the R code that creates the code for a SQLDeveloper table (shown below), create a NewYork table in SQL Developer and import the data from the csv data set.

  1. for the first plot: after reading the file, wrangle and plot sex by number of deaths(Count_) for each ethnicity in the year 2011 by females and males. Each dot represents a different cause of death.

  2. For the second plot: Plot each ethnicitys percentage of death due to heart diseases for the years 2007 - 2011. Each dot represents a different years ethnicitys percent of death (Percent_). Some years overlap with one another, which is why there arent 5 full bullets per ethnicity.

  3. For the third plot: Plots the percent of deaths (Percent_) of both Asian & Pacific Islander males and females per specific disease from 2007 - 2011.

  4. ALSO INCLUDES HEAD AND SUMMARY AT THE BOTTOM
